---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Bandish and Classical Composition | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Learn to play classical compositions in Drut (fast) and Vilambit (slow) tempos. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Bandish and Classical Composition</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-advanced capitalize">advanced</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 45 min · Advanced</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Bandish and Classical Composition</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Learn to play classical compositions in Drut (fast) and Vilambit (slow) tempos.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Bandish = fixed composition in a specific raga and taal</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Sthayi = refrain in lower and middle octave</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Antara = second section exploring upper octave</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Vilambit = slow tempo (16–60 BPM per beat)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Drut = fast tempo (120+ BPM per beat)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>What is a Bandish</h2>
      <p>A bandish is a fixed pre-composed melodic poem set to a specific raga and taal. Unlike improvisation every note of a bandish remains the same each performance. Mastering bandishes gives structure to your playing reveals how raga grammar is applied in organized musical form and gives you concrete material to perform for others.</p>

      <h2>Structure of a Bandish</h2>
      <p>Every bandish has two main sections. The Sthayi (refrain) is typically in Mandra and Madhya saptak and is sung or played multiple times throughout the performance. The Antara (second section) explores the Taar saptak. After Antara the performer returns to Sthayi. Improvisation fills the space between each repetition of these fixed sections.</p>

      <h2>Learning Vilambit Bandish</h2>
      <p>Vilambit (slow) compositions use very slow taal cycles giving maximum space for expression ornamentation and emotional depth. Practice the Yaman bandish from the Raga Yaman lesson in Vilambit Teentaal at 40 BPM per cycle. This extreme slowness forces you to ornament and express each note — essential for developing true classical playing quality.</p>

      <h2>Learning Drut Bandish</h2>
      <p>Drut (fast) compositions require precision finger speed and clean articulation. Take the same Yaman bandish and practice it in Drut Teentaal at 120 BPM. Start very slowly and increase tempo 5 BPM per week. The contrast between playing the same bandish in Vilambit then Drut tempo — showing the raga from two completely different perspectives — is a fundamental classical performance technique.</p>

      <h2>Performance Structure</h2>
      <p>A complete classical performance typically begins with Alaap (no rhythm slow exploration) then Jod (rhythmic but no tabla) then Jhala (fast rhythmic) then the Bandish in Vilambit tempo with improvisation then the same Bandish in Madhya (medium) tempo then Drut tempo. Understanding this structure helps you organize any raga into a satisfying complete musical presentation.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>